cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper deals with machine learning and bias reduction in data sets, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The application of the methodology to the detection of irregular power usage suggests that it could also fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as detecting electricity theft is a security concern. Additionally, the use of real, noisy industrial data implies that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as it deals with data from a real-world system. Finally, the mention of high-dimensional data sets suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
